1. Install your liked OS. I prefer Debian Linux
2. In command lone use next command: python3 --version 
    if all correct then next step. Else install python3
3. Install git in your system. Also apt install git
4. Create folder workhistory. Also mkdir /home/user_name/workhistory
5. cd /home/user_name/workhistory
6. git clone https://github.com/saibogo/work_history.git
7. apt install pip
8. apt install python3-psycopg2
9. apt install python3-flask
10. apt install python3-psutil
11. pip3 install fpdf
12. apt install python3-pyqt5
12.1. pip3 install aiogram
12.2. create bot. get token and create file 'telegram_token.txt'
12.3. edit config.xml section path_to_telegram_token
13. apt install postgresql
14. su  (And insert your superuser password)
15. su - postgres
16. psql -Upostgres
17. =# CREATE USER saibogo WITH PASSWORD 'myPassword';
18. =# CREATE DATABASE workhistory;
19. =# GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DATABASE "workhistory" to saibogo;
20. =# \c workhistory
21. workhistory=# GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON ALL TABLES IN SCHEMA public TO "saibogo";
22. exit to normal terminal
23. psql workhistory < /path/to/your/dump.db
24. python3 /path/to/main.py --help
25. cd to static dir in your project
26. gzip -dr equips   This command unpack all details files
Well Done!
27. edit config.xml in your favorite editor (patches and ip)
28. python3 /path/to/main.py --help
29. python3 /path/to/main.py --allstart
30. in your browser go to to http://your_ip:5000
Well Done!

29. To add user in telegramm-bot add records in read_bot_access.py and write_bot_access.py
30. Server use HTTPS. Certificate and privateKey in folder wh_app/cert. Generated with using openssl

